name: At Home: Glassroots Recycling in New Orleans
summary: This week Mike and the team head to The Big Easy to meet up with Max Steitz and Franziska Trautmann, who after a bottle of wine one night, found themselves frustrated by New Orleans' lack of glass recycling. One thing led to another, and Glass Half Full was born; A grassroots glass recycling program that turns glass bottles into sand and cullet for disaster relief and prevention.

name: Дмитрий Марков и Поля из деревки там, куда редко ездят по своей воле
December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 1, 6:10am
summary: In this episode: Japan's meticulous planning and preparation made it possible to surprise the Americans at Pearl Harbor. Alert on Oahu is largely nonexistent. It is the deep breath before the plunge.

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 2, 6:40am
summary: There are signals of attack and a buzz of chatter in the air, but will this be enough to force the American defenders out of their beds?

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 3, 7:10am
summary: In this episode: War is sort of declared, but Japanese planes have already started their attack.

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 4, 7:40am
summary: In this episode: The first wave commences its attack, how successful will it be? Will months of planning and preparation pay off?

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 5, 8:10am
summary: The first wave continues, and with it, the chaos and destruction.

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 6, 8:40am
summary: Desperate and shocked, American forces scramble to mount a resistance to the attack. But how effective can this be as the Japanese launch their second decisive raid?

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 7, 9:10am
summary: American pilots are in the air, defending Pearl Harbor. They have already lost so much, and the Japanese show no sign of letting up the attack. How much will the Americans accomplish with their defense?

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 8, 9:40am
summary: The Japanese attack is over, but the damage is done and the remaining Americans in Hawaii are left to react to their defeat.

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 9, 10:10am
summary: Today marks the beginning of a war all over the South Pacific and Southeast Asia. How will the world change from here?

name: December 7, 1941: Pearl Harbor Minute by Minute in Real Time - Part 10, 10:40am
summary: The circle closes, and we see why these fateful decisions were made and what the United States' reaction will be.

name: CHAHHAN&RYO　YUKI&SHIORI&TOHKO
summary:
After listening to the original song of 'No. 77', 'Yuki Ebana' was convinced that it was a song she sang for herself, and headed to the place where she used to live on the street, where she sang 'No. 77'. Discover the boy. The song 'No. 77' was made with the boy's singing in mind, Yuki.
Yuki tells her boy that their debut song is 'No. 77' made by the boy, and she takes the boy to meet her office president 'Yuichi Yanagishita'. The boy and Yanagishita will have a discussion together.
She returns and she tells the story to 'Ryo', 'Shiori Kato' and 'Hitoko Murakami'. Hitoko wonders if the boy is destined for Yuki. Ryo tells us that he wants to see you guys debut and play an active part as soon as possible, even if it's a human song.
However, the boy did not respond to Yanagishita's persuasion, and he refused to let him use his song. Ryo appeared to Yanagishita who was in trouble and said, 'Leave him to me.'
